    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1791348f_f08e2e55",
        "filename": "tests/CodecTest.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 20
      },
      "lineNbr": 1003,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-07-19T14:41:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "What are you trying to test here? The name makes it look like you want to test progressive decoding, or at least a progressive image. dog.jpg is not a progressive image, and calling getAndroidPixels does not do a progressive decode.\n\nAgain, we already have a test for this. Look at tests/CodecPartialTest.cpp",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1003,
        "startChar": 9,
        "endLine": 1003,
        "endChar": 31
      },
      "revId": "b7484498176faade2042db0ee49408505341a791",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "13abfab1_ad04c97c",
        "filename": "tests/CodecTest.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 20
      },
      "lineNbr": 1010,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-07-19T14:41:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This line doesn\u0027t really change anything. MakeSubset gives you a subset of the data, in this case from 0, to data-\u003esize(), which is the full size of the data.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1010,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 1010,
        "endChar": 59
      },
      "revId": "b7484498176faade2042db0ee49408505341a791",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8198dd20_57d832a7",
        "filename": "tests/CodecTest.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 20
      },
      "lineNbr": 1011,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-07-19T14:41:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "SkAndroidCodec will test incremental decoding, but only if you request sampling, which you do not do. This will just test getPixels. You want to call startIncrementalDecode/incrementalDecode which call the methods you added to SkJpegCodec, onStartIncrementalDecode and onIncrementalDecode. (Skia often follows a pattern of a non-virtual public method, e.g. publicMethod(), which calls a virtual protected method with the same name but starting with \"on\", e.g. onPublicMethod().)\n\nBut again, there\u0027s already a test for this. It\u0027s in CodecPartialTest.cpp. You shouldn\u0027t have to write much code here; just something like:\n\n  test_partial(\"dog.jpg\");",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1011,
        "startChar": 42,
        "endLine": 1011,
        "endChar": 69
      },
      "revId": "b7484498176faade2042db0ee49408505341a791",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
